  "abstract": "ICGV 86031 (Reg. no. GP-58, PI no. 561917) is a spanishtype\r\npeanut (Arachis hypogaea L. subsp. fastigiata Waldron\r\nvar. vulgaris Hartz) developed at the International Crops Research\r\nInstitute for the Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT), Patancheru,\r\nIndia. It was released in 1991 by the Plant Materials\r\nIdentification Committee of ICRISAT because of its resistance\r\nto thrips (Thripspalmi Karny), jassid (Empoasca kerri Pruthi),\r\nspodoptera [Spodoptera litura (Fabricius)], groundnut leaf miner\r\n(Aproaerema modicella Deventer) and bud necrosis virus (BNV),\r\nwhich causes bud necrosis disease (END) in peanut. ICGV\r\n86031 has also been found to be photoperiod insensitive and\r\nresistant to iron deficiency chlorosis (4).",
